definition.value: An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA having succinoyl as the S-acyl component.
An optically active form of limonene having (4R)-configuration.
A beta-D-Galp-(1->2)-D-Glcp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hyoxy group has alpha configuration.
An optically active form of limonene having (4S)-configuration.
A monoterpene that is cyclohex-1-ene substituted by a methyl group at position 1 and a prop-1-en-2-yl group at position 4 respectively.
